This paper deals with image processing using deep learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training the network using residual learning, which is a popular technique in deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. Additionally, the paper deals with image super-resolution, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves training the network using a specific strategy, which could fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
